@u2hmtmkmkm

A year late, but better late than never. The DVD creator needs to convert the videos to MPEG-2, a significantly less efficient codec than Xvid, H.264, or MPEG4. Thus, much larger file sizes. 

Hell, if H.264 was around when DVDs were invented, we would probably be using CDs for movies, because of the much smaller file size.
